6  pca

import lets_plot
import scanpy as sc
from lets_plot import *

import cellestial as cl

LetsPlot.setup_html()

data = sc.read("data/pbmc3k_pped.h5ad")

6.0.1 By default, the pca function will use “leiden” as the key

plot = cl.pca(data,axis_type="arrow",size=0.6, interactive=True)
plot

6.1 Of course, it is possible to customize the plot

plot + scale_color_hue()

6.2 You can also use a gene a key.

cl.pca(data, "NEAT1", color_high="#D2042D")
print(
    f"lets_plot: {lets_plot.__version__}",
    f"scanpy: {sc.__version__}",
    f"cellestial: {cl.__version__}",
    sep="\n"
)
lets_plot: 4.5.2
scanpy: 1.10.4
cellestial: 0.1.4
